    h2 
        + Getting started
    h3 
        + 1. Create an api.video free account
    ul 
        ordered 
        li 
            + Go to
            a 
                href https://dashboard.api.video/
                title 
                + dashboard.api.video
            + , log in or create a free account.
        li 
            + You can choose to stay in sandbox and have watermark over your videos, or enter in
            a 
                href https://api.video/pricing
                title 
                + production mode
            + and take advantage of all the features without limitations.
    br 
    h3 
        + 2. Get you API key
    ul 
        ordered 
        li 
            + Once in the dashboard, find your API keys directly in the
            code /overview
            + or navigate to
            code /apikeys
            + with the &quot;API Keys&quot; button in the side navigation.
        li 
            + Copy your API key, and paste it in
            code .env.local.example
            + as value for
            code API_KEY
            + .
        li 
            + Rename
            code .env.local.example
            + to
            code .env.local
            + .
        li 
            + Install the packages by running
            code npm install
            + ,
            code yarn install
            + or
            code pnpm install
            + .
        li 
            + You can now try the application locally by running
            code npm run dev
            + ,
            code yarn dev
            + or
            code pnpm dev
            + from the root directory.
    br 
    h3 
        + 3. Deployment
    ul 
        ordered 
        li 
            + First, push your app to GitHub/GitLab or Bitbucket
        li 
            + Then, go to
            a 
                href https://vercel.com?utm_source=github&utm_medium=readme&utm_campaign=next-example
                title 
                + Vercel
            + and import your new repository.
        li 
            + Add an environment variable with name
            code API_KEY
            + and your API key for value.
        li 
